# Indentation: four spaces per level

Use **four spaces** as the width of **one indentation level** everywhere in this project.

## Tabs vs spaces

- If the file or toolchain uses **tab characters** (`\t`), they must be **equivalent to four spaces**: editor tab size **4**, and nested structure should read as multiples of 4 columns.
- If the file uses **spaces**, indent with **4 spaces** per level (not 2).

## Examples

```typescript
// ✅ GOOD: each nested block +4 spaces (or one tab = 4 columns)
function example() {
    if (condition) {
        doWork();
    }
}
```

```typescript
// ❌ BAD: 2-space indent when project standard is 4
function example() {
  if (condition) {
    doWork();
  }
}
```

When editing, set **Tab Size** and **Indent** to **4** so aligns with collaborators and formatters.
